parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: A strengthened form of a primary teko tek'-o; to produce, literally or figuratively.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive Feminine 3rd Person Singular
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
First-born, eldest. From protos and the alternate of tikto; first-born.
A son, descendent. Apparently a primary word; a 'son', used very widely of immediate, remote or figuratively, kinship.

word: She wrapped Him in swaddling cloths
parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To swathe, wrap in swaddling clothes. From sparganon; to swathe.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To lay upon, lean against, lay down, make to recline; pass: I lie back, recline. From ana and klino; to lean back.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Accusative Masculine 3rd Person Singular
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.
A manger, feeding-trough, stall. From pateomai; a crib.
On this account, because, for. From dia and hoti; on the very account that, or inasmuch as.

parse: Verb - Imperfect Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
No, not. Also ouk, and ouch a primary word; the absolute negative adverb; no or not.
Apparently a primary word; a spot, i.e. Location; figuratively, condition, opportunity; specially, a scabbard.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Dative Masculine 3rd Person Plural
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
An inn, lodging-place. From kataluo; properly, a dissolution, i.e. a lodging-place.
